correctness.rationale: Several key fields are incorrect, not traceable, or mixed from a different ALD step, despite some correct entries (PEALD method, precursors DADI/TMGa/DEZ, O2 plasma 100 W, 200 °C, 1.2 Torr, 6:1:1 supercycle, TG-BC device metrics). Major issues: (1) Dosing/purging times (0.1 s, 25 s, 5 s, 20 s) and their units (ms) are wrongly assigned to IGZO sub-cycles; these times are reported for Al2O3 GI ALD, not IGZO, and units are incorrect (seconds in the article vs milliseconds in JSON). (2) Growth per cycle (0.9 Å) is taken from Al2O3 GPC trend; no GPCs are reported for In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO, so these values are ungrounded. (3) numberofCycles = 6 with filmThickness = 30 nm is inconsistent with the reported process and GPC; device IGZO thickness is 8 nm while a separate stacked film used 30 nm—mixing samples. (4) Flow rates, saturation, nucleationPeriod are not reported; values are fabricated. (5) Uniformity (0.01%) and conformality aspect ratio (10) are not given in the article. (6) Optical properties: refractive index 1.62 corresponds to Al2O3 (Figure S5), not IGZO; absorption coefficient not reported; band gap 2.8 eV is plausible for as-deposited IGZO but context (before/after anneal) is not specified. (7) Electrical properties: resistivity 1.34 ohm·m conflicts with reported conductivity (1.34 S/cm → ~0.0746 ohm·m); carrier density is not reported; mobility here duplicates device mobility and is misplaced under material properties. (8) Film composition: atomic ratio set to 1.0:2.8:5.4 and “elementalConcentration” 11.2% do not match the XRF composition In0.52 Ga0.18 Zn0.30 O; O 1s peak fractions are not elemental concentrations. (9) Film density 3.12 uses the Al2O3 GI value and the unit (g/dm3) does not match the source (g/cm3). (10) onOffRatio 1e6 not reported. (11) purgingGas = Ar for IGZO is not explicitly stated (only carrier gas Ar is). Correct/Review: dosingTime/purgeTime units and provenance; remove unreported flowRates/saturation/nucleationPeriod; correct GPC/numberofCycles/filmThickness to match reported IGZO films; fix optical/electrical properties to IGZO-only and with correct units; update filmComposition to In0.52:Ga0.18:Zn0.30; remove unreported uniformity/conformality/roughness; correct film density or omit if not reported; ensure device metrics correspond to the specific GI deposition temperature (400 °C) device context.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and incomplete relative to both the article and the schema. Major issues: (1) Missing process: The paper reports two distinct ALD processes (IGZO active layer via PEALD and Al2O3 gate insulator via thermal ALD with TMA/O3). Only one process is provided, and GI deposition (vertical-flow reactor, 350 mTorr, O3 reactant at 200–400 °C with explicit dose/purge times 0.1 s/25 s/5 s/20 s) is not represented as a separate process as required by the schema’s multi-process guidance (Sec. 2.2). (2) Misattribution/mixing of processes: The dosing and purge times listed (0.1 s, 25 s, 5 s, 20 s) are for Al2O3 GI (Sec. 2.2) but are incorrectly assigned to In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO sub-cycles of IGZO; time units are also wrong (entered as milliseconds in the schema, not seconds). Refractive index (1.62–1.63) and density trends (to 3.12 g/cm3) reported for Al2O3 are incorrectly assigned under IGZO material properties. (3) Ungrounded/fabricated values: Flow rates (10 sccm for precursor/co-reactant/purge), saturation, nucleation period, uniformity (0.01%), conformality aspect ratio (10), roughness (0.5 nm), on/off ratio (1e6) are not reported anywhere in the article and thus are not traceable. (4) Composition errors: The reported IGZO composition is In0.52Ga0.18Zn0.30O (XRF). The extracted atomic ratio ‘1.0:2.8:5.4’ and elemental concentration ‘11.2%’ (which seems to be misused from an Odef XPS peak fraction) are incorrect and not traceable. (5) Electrical properties misassigned/wrong units: The conductivity of the IGZO active layer after 600 °C anneal is 1.34 S/cm (Sec. 3.2, Fig. 3c), so resistivity should be ~7.46×10^-3 Ω·m, not 1.34 Ω·m. The ‘mobility’ under materialProperties is labeled as Hall but uses device field‑effect mobility (27.6 cm2/Vs) from TFTs. (6) Cycle count mis-specified: numberofCycles is set to 6, but the article only defines a supercycle ratio (6:1:1) and does not report total cycles; this is not traceable. (7) Pressure/temperature/reactant for IGZO are mostly correct (200 °C, 1.2 Torr, O2 plasma 100 W), and the supercycle design (6 In2O3, 1 Ga2O3, 1 ZnO) is correct, but the process still mixes in GI parameters. To be complete and schema-compliant: add a second process for ALD-Al2O3 (TMA/O3, 200–400 °C, 350 mTorr, O3 concentration 200 g/m3, reported dose/purge times); correct IGZO dosing/purge times (not reported—should not be fabricated), remove untraceable flow rates/uniformity/conformality/roughness or clearly ground them; fix composition (use In:Ga:Zn = 0.52:0.18:0.30 or normalized), correct resistivity and method labels, and revise numberofCycles and film properties to match reported data.
